                alt="Screenshot of a webpage showing library hours in a month view"
                caption="Figure 9: Month view of library hours on the new website"
                width="100%"
                height="100%"
                />
            <Figure
                path="/src/assets/images/mobileWeekView.png"
                alt="Screenshot of a webpage showing library hours in a week view on a mobile device"
                caption="Figure 10: Week view of library hours on the new website on a mobile device"
                width="100%"
                height="100%"
                />
            <Figure
                path="/src/assets/images/mobileMonthView.png"
                alt="Screenshot of a webpage showing library hours in a month view on a mobile device"
                caption="Figure 11: Month view of library hours on the new website on a mobile device"
                width="100%"
                height="100%"
                />
        </div>
        <h2>Library Spaces Discovery Interface Redesign and Development</h2>
        <p>
            Inspired by the work of NCSU Libraries, we set out to redesign and enhance the interface used by patrons to explore and discover library spaces. The previous system (Figure 12) featured a Netflix-style horizontal scrolling layout, which presented significant accessibility challenges and limited user interaction.
        </p>
        <p>
            Collaborating with UX Designer Shelby Kroske, we envisioned a new interface that would be fast, responsive, and intuitive. This effort required extensive research into both user-centered design principles and technical implementation strategies. Shelby designed a dynamic, list-style interface that adapts in real time to user preferences, offering a more accessible and streamlined experience.
        </p>
        <p>
            On the development side, I built a custom Drupal module capable of querying our search index to retrieve available space data. The module dynamically updates the displayed records based on user-selected filters, ensuring a seamless and personalized discovery process (Figure 13). I took extra care to ensure that this new interface is accessible by having it tested by our students in the Accessibility unit and addressing their concerns from the early stages of development.
        </p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 bg-gray-800 bg-clip-padding rounded px-2">
            <Figure
                path="/src/assets/images/oldSpaces.png"
                alt="Screenshot of a webpage showing library spaces in a grid layout"
                caption="Figure 12: Discover library spaces on the old website"
                width="100%"
                height="100%"
                />
            <Figure
                path="/src/assets/images/newSpaces.png"
                alt="Screenshot of a webpage showing library spaces in a list layout"
                caption="Figure 13: Discover library spaces interface on the new website"
                width="100%"
                height="100%"
                />
        </div>
        <p>The new version of our main library website was launched on Aug 17th, 2023.</p>
